description._content:
Call No.: 12_00238
Year: 1937
Corp. Name: Zeppelin
Subject: Zeppelin
Notes: ""Survives Hindenburg disaster: lakehurst, N.J., May 6--this woman is being led from the scene of the crash of the giant German Zeppelin, Hindenburg, which burst into flames as it was being nosed toward the mooring mast at the Naval Air Station here. A passenger on the ship, she was on the fortunate few to escape. The fatality list was undetermined.""
Description: 7 x 9 Black and White Photo
